<p>Greenlight thread:<br />
<a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13886219/greenlight-request-frozen-corpse-and-nervous-system">http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13886219/greenlight-request-frozen-corpse-and-nervous-system</a></p>
<p>Sandbox article:<br />
<a href="http://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/gopher-chucks">http://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/gopher-chucks</a></p>
<p>Sorry for the wait on this; the holiday season was busy, the audio took some time to record/edit, and I took a while to figure out the Sandbox.</p>
<p>Anyway, this is my first completed draft of my SCP hopeful. I'm hoping for an overall review, but a few specific things I'm hoping to hear about:<br />
-I intended to make the skip both unnerving and sympathetic to the reader/listener. How did I do?<br />
-I presented the series of events in relatively vague terms, and in the order of the Foundation learning about them, which is out of chronological order, so that the reader can piece together the story on their own. Am I being too obvious, not obvious enough, or is there another issue in how this is presented?<br />
-Is the length okay? (word count is 2496)</p>
<p>Also, just a general question, since I couldn't find a clear answer in the guides, but does a draft need an official greenlight before being uploaded to the site, or can it be uploaded as soon as the writer is confident in it?</p>
<p>Thanks!</p>

